; ------------------------------------------------------------
; Per-dog race-tick state machines (dog1..dog6)
; ------------------------------------------------------------
; Each dog has an identical ~300-line state machine structure:
;   1. 50% chance to enter a random slowdown branch.
;   2. Pick a "speed tier" based on displayOddsTop[i] (dogs 1-3)
;      or displayOddsBottom[i-3] (dogs 4-6). Lower odds = faster.
;      Dog 1 additionally branches on dogInfo.affection when the
;      player dog is in the race (bit 5).
;   3. Within each tier, roll again to pick a step size; update
;      varN (the per-dog counter) and SET_FRAME_DELTA to animate.
; The state machines keep looping until .cs_race swaps them out
; via SET_OTHER_EXECUTOR_PTR to .dog_slowdown_after_finish.

.dog1_race_tick:
    BRANCH_ON_RANDOM 0, 50, .branch_1413AC

